# exponential decay curve — 16 points matching 808 hardware RC discharge
( 1 .82 .67 .54 .44 .35 .28 .22 .17 .13 .09 .07 .04 .025 .012 .003 )
/d300
# v19: one-shot exponential decay modulator
# f3 = plays over ~333ms, drives amplitude of v23 and v24
# must be in H chain — one-shot requires l1+ to start
v19 w300,1,1 a0 t 0 1 0 0 f 3 m1
# v23: saw at 540Hz — provides 540, 1080, 1620, 2160Hz harmonic series
# v24: square at 812Hz — dominant fundamental, lowpass kills 2436Hz harmonic
# v25: noise transient — short attack click
v23 w2 a-10 t 0 .350 0 0 f 540 q0 J1 K 2500 Q 0.35 A19,1.0,0.0 H24,25,19,-1
v24 w1 a2   t 0 .380 0 0 f 812 q0 J1 K 1100 Q 0.40 A19,1.0,0.0
v25 w6 a6   t 0 .015 0 0 q1 J0 l1
v23l1
